I say all this as someone who had to leave church because I tried to move the needle too fast and burnt myself out. I moved beyond and I know my triggers(lgbt+ issues). I say this all out of love for y’all. Love and care for your sanity and joy. Don’t let any of it take your joy.

Many may disagree with me. Maybe you got the all or nothing and you had to take the big leap. But that doesn’t work for a lot of people. The doubt and fear can drive them into even deeper fundamentalism. Let them have baby food. Show them a real steak when they are ready.

But if it triggers? Don’t read it or listen to it. Call out the blatant stuff ( like saying deconstruction means the end of faith that you probably never had). But let some of the rest that has good feed those who need it…
Know when you’re well beyond something. Be prepared to help someone move beyond that. But let them take a baby step first. We all had to do so. It’s just easy to forget when you’re on the other side…

Is the other really baby food? Yeah but to them, it’s like a steak dinner. I’ve seen it so many times. And it’s hard being someone sitting and going “but that’s just basic. There is more. That’s still not freedom that’s just fuzzy handcuffs(not the fun kind).”

There are people who need to hear the good. They need to hear things like I’m not going to hell if I like sex. That women’s orgasms need to be considered. That you can miss Sunday church and be ok. Those who need to hear it aren’t gonna listen to us well on the other side of it…

I know there are people who are repacking elements of purity culture, etc, softening the blow and fixing some things. it’s right to critique it. But some of us who are well beyond need not engage. Some are called, not all. Don’t trigger yourself because bitter isn’t healing…
